<text>My just-turned-1 year old son chipped his tooth and we had just moved to the area, so I went to yelp to find a dentist and started calling to see who could take us ASAP. Lollipop office said they could that afternoon and could see my 4yr old as well, just for a cleaning which nice and convenient. They took all our contact and insurance card information over the phone.  We showed up 15 mins early to be able to fill out the rest of the forms since we were new patients.  After sitting down and waiting 10mins the receptionist informed us that whoever we spoke to on the phone (we spoke with her) scheduled the appointment for tomorrow. After re-explaining the situation they were able to fit us in, and handed us forms to complete via iPad. It was asking for all the information we had previously provided over the phone.  They got us in 45 mins after our original appointment time.  The hygienist and dentist were professional and polite.  But it definitely felt impersonal. The experience overall was fine, but it was tedious and annoying to have to give that information over the phone and then retype it into an iPad twice (once per kid) all the while the 1 with a chipped tooth is screaming.  If the receptionists could focus on the tasks at hand and stop worrying about being so sickly sweet and get to the point, that would‚Äôve helped in this situation.< /text>< UserId.>

<userid>109145387430997778002<//userid>< Text>
I have taken a few tours in LA, and different cities around the world, and LA City Tours gave the best tour from start to finish.  I wanted to see as much of LA as I could in one day, so I went on the A1 6 hour tour with 5 scheduled stops.  The tour allows a fair amount of time at each stop, and you get to see and learn so much of LA in a relatively short period of time.  All while on a comfortable, air conditioned bus.
We saw Hollywood, Griffith Park, Downtown LA, Santa Monica, Beverly Hills, and so much more.  My advice is to be on time at each stop, and be considerate of the other passengers on the bus.  Also, it's customary to tip the guide for an appreciation of good service.  Thanks to LA City Tours for a fantastic experience.< /Text>

Took the Hollywood plus LA plus beaches plus celebrity tour. It was 6 hours long and gave us a pretty complete overview of the area which is what we were looking for, so that is my 3 stars. If they would have stuck to the sights and famous places that "make" the area - and gave us opportunity to take a photograph at each - it would have been better. There were no ear phones (even though there were places for them) and the two half hour stops were too short. You have the impression that they have to do the tour in the shortest time as possible $$$, so he drove all times w speeds above the average traffic speed. The tour started at 9:40 and went to 1:00 pm, so deducting the two 1/2 h stops it just lasted 2:20 hours for $70 price per passenger. Later, we also learned that some of the information about famous actresses/ actors property residences were wrongly identified. I do not recommended it to anybody. Find another company with a relaxed driver w a company that allows him/her to drive w more time and also w good sense of humor and patience! Stressed trip overall!<//Review><Pics>None<//Pics>< Response>

tour.  The bus arrived on time to the minute.

bathroom at the tour office.  There is only
one bathroom and there is a long line.

one bathroom.

< text>
Had an amazing time on the 6 hour city tour with LA City Tours! The staff at the front desk was very nice and made us feel welcome.
We had about 20 minutes to walk around Hollywood Blvd. before the tour started, which was just enough time to get the flavor and take some cool photos of the stars on the sidewalk.
The tour stopped at every place that we were told was a "must see" before we came out to California! Including, The Griffith Park Observatory, Farmers Market, the big sign in Beverly Hills (amazing photo op) and Santa Monica, which was just lovely! Can't beat the fresh ocean breeze.
The bus was clean and comfortable and our driver was very knowledgable and fun.
It was a fantastic day and I totally recommend LA City Tours! 5 Stars!</text>

<pics>None< /pics><Date>1503632340932< /Date><Review>To summon me and my boyfriend's experiences of the tour, I unfortunately have to say that we were very disappointed. First of all we thought that the tour would be held in an open-roof doubledecker, alternatively in a bus with open windows. Second of all, we thought that we would get a good look at the Hollywood-sign, and of some stars' homes in Hollywood/Beverly Hills.

In reality, the tour was given in a tiny bus with closed windows, which might be good to know if any of you are planning on taking pictures. Also, it means that everytime the driver points out something outside the opposite side of the bus, you wont really see much at all. Second of all, we didn't actually get to see any homes up close. We did, however, see a bunch of gates in Hollywood Hills, which apparently lead into the actual neighborhoods of the stars. Though, we did get to see a woodenfence, which is said to be covering a realestate owned by Justin Timberlake. Also, we got to see a house belonging to Charlie Sheen. Or at least something beige, that is said to be a building, seen from hundreds of meters away. And the Hollywood-sign, well, it was so far away we could barely read the letters.

In spite of all of the negative things listed above, I would like to point out that we had a wonderful driver who really did his best to make our experience as amusing and interesting as possible. I am very disappointed in their service here. I introduce my mom to this store due to their great prices and I would find great deals. However, lately they have been not as great as before. We've come here as our first store buying some MK braclete for $29 and when you buy 2 or more they are an additional 20Ÿ™ off. We went around the outlet and realized we forgot to buy a couple more gifts for my sisters and that they would live one. When we came back a couple of hours later they decided to change the price because of the sales. They are now charging $39 each braclete and no longer give 20% off. I inform my mom that we should just leave because that is messed up how they tried to charge more.
The following day my friend wanted to go to the outlet and buy some things for Christmas. We so happen to come back in the store so that I can show her what my mom bought. They told us that the braclete are $29 and 20% off when you buy 2 or more. I was very offended how they lied to me the day before.
Please be sure when you purchase anything from them that you have no issue because they will be sure to not help you at all. They have some type of deal with Fossil who are the manufacturer for all watches and brand you see there. That is how they can offer such deals. Be advised that they do not repair at all and when they send it out they will also send you the bill.</review>

< text>
Came here to purchase a watch after the Christmas rush - and ended up choosing a Marc by Marc Jacobs watch that I liked at the time. Workers were friendly and helpful as they helped me compare several models of watches before I finally chose the one I wanted.

However, Watch Station adjusts the watch to your size and fit if you want to get it fitted before leaving the store. I decided to wait in line and get my watch fitted - bad choice. They took a ton of time taking out the links to get the band to fit my wrist. And the links that they returned to me were broken and no longer could be used. Clearly the worker who had adjusted the watch did not know what he was doing, so sadly the links I have no longer can be used. At the time, I hadn't bothered to check on the links - but now that I am back at home, I can clearly see the amount of force that was used to remove the links from the watch.

tl;dr - Buying a watch here is no problem, but I don't recommend getting it sized and fitted. Take it somewhere else.< /text>

< Review>
The sushi sashimi combo was great. Ordered the large and it fed 5 of us.
Came with porridge, oyster shots, korean pancakes, corn cheese, salad, tempura with shrimp, egg steam, sea urchin, sea squirt, salmon collar grilled, California roll, tempura roll, live halibut sashimi,  yellow tail, salmon, tuna, red snapper, mackerel, and etc side dishes.
To top it all off , at the end, a spicy seafood soup with your choice of cooked burnt rice soften in water or rice.
$210. Included the tip. Not to shabby....
Yummy . . .
P.s. Try the assorted (haedupbop)sashimi spicy rice bowl.
Hella good......<//Review>

Sally Elbassir</username>
<Review>Love this place and I've had a lot of sushi. My mom, who doesn't even like sushi, enjoyed this place.
We ordered the las vegas roll, a bento box with beef, and another roll (rainbow I think?).
The bento box was disappointing (I just wasn't digging the flavor), but it very generously came with a ton of side dishes, sashimi, rice, beef, and tempura veggies.
We all got some miso soup as well (it comes with the meal--yum).
The sushi was to die for. Crispy and delicious, and very fresh. I was tempted to order more, but was simply too full. The only downfall is their lack of happy hour but that really is it. If you're here for sushi, you've made the right choice.
We ordered the las vegas roll, a bento box with beef, and another roll (rainbow I think?).
The bento box was disappointing (I just wasn't digging the flavor), but it very generously came with a ton of side dishes, sashimi, rice, beef, and tempura veggies.
We all got some miso soup as well (it comes with the meal--yum).
The sushi was to die for. Crispy and delicious, and very fresh. I was tempted to order more, but was simply too full. The only downfall is their lack of happy hour (at least I'm pretty sure they dont) but that really is it. If you're here for sushi, you've made the right choice.< /Review><user_id>109402086603161483632<//user_id></record></dataset><record>

I have been going to Primary Eyecare Optometric for several years now and I have found it to be an exceptional office. From the friendly receptionists, who great you on the way in, to the technicians, who perform all sorts of eye tests quickly and thoroughly, to Dr. Dea, who expertly evaluates my eyesight and prescribes the perfect prescription for my needs, they all do so while also answering all my questions and even carrying on meaningful conversations! < review>
I would not recommend this place. I had made an appointment and had waited several weeks only to have my appointment canceled just hours before I was scheduled to arrive. No explanation was given and I was only told someone would call to reschedule the appointment on the following Monday.
Monday came and went and there was no followup. I called and was greeted with an automated message that the office had been exposed to COVID-19 (Corona Virus.) This was never explained when my appointment was canceled nor was it communicated to me at a later point. DID PRIMARY EYECARE EVEN WARN THE CLIENTS THAT WERE EXPOSED? I can't be sure but their unprofessionalism would cause me concern.
Several days later and I still haven't been contacted about rescheduling.  Once again It was up to me to call the office and get a status update. The receptionist lied and said they were open Monday (even though they were letting an automated message do their dirt work that same Monday) And I had to pry what happened out of her. She said she would set up a new appointment for me... IN THREE WEEKS.
I understand there is a global pandemic and everyone is running a little short staffed or under duress. But it doesn't make sense that I should have to go nearly a month and a half without an appointment because of their mismanagement. <user>110986693894727440936<//user>< pictures>
None</pictures>
< Review>
I have been fortunate enough to have Dr. Osias as my Optometrist for a number of years.  Dr. Osias is like an old friend, and he treats me as such, he knows about my preexisting conditions and always keeps a watchful eye on my eye's and eye wear.
Normally, I see Dr. Osias for my annual eye exam, however this year I ran into a bit of trouble with my Primary Physicians request that I get an eye screening at Kaiser.  Kaiser "found" a problem with my eyes with the pictures they took. Not only did this put a good scare into me it also added a lot of stress to my world.
Dr. Osias was happy to recheck my eyes, and run a new Optomap series of images on my eyes even though I had a series of pics done in February at my annual check up.  Dr. Osias worked with me to figure out what Kaiser had likely seen. It turned out Dr. Osias had already seen the issue and was watching it. He collected data and drafted a note for the people at Kaiser, explaining his findings and the promise that IF my eye's developed a problem he would without hesitation direct me to the right people to get any corrective action taken.
I have loyalty to Dr. Osias, that only comes with years of working together, trust and mutual respect.
Primary Eyecare has been there for me when i was a cash paying customer as well as when I had insurance.  They have always tried to work with me to save money, and they are flexible in working around my schedule.
I would and will recommend Dr. Osias without any hesitation.< /Review>

< review>
Oh my God Becky, look at her lunch... I love Japanese bento and had to visit The Grubbies after spotting it on Yelp. It's a little take out window with Japanese signage and a big drum next to it. The line was pretty long during lunch but after I spotted the uni and ikura lunch set I decided to commit to the process. It took about 15 minutes for us to get up the window but the ordering process was fast. I ordered my lunch set, paid and got to make a wish and hit the giant drum. Oh yes! This is what I call true entertainment! My lunch came wrapped in a beautiful blue scarf and I carried it back to the office to unwrap like a wonderful Christmas present. My uni and ikura lunch came with rice, miso soup and nori. Each bite was everything I wanted in the perfect Japanese comfort food lunch and for me it was well worth the hefty $35 price tag. They have cheaper lunch sets and I definitely recommend ordering ahead to avoid the lunchtime wait!< /review>

<rate>5</rate>< Text>
They're great! When I suspected one of my small dogs has food allergies, my mom recommended Paws... I walked in and was greeted by friendly knowledgeable people that listened, gave me options in different price ranges, and explained everything. No hard sell on the expensive stuff, just information! I left with a shampoo that's amazing (Micro-Tek) to help relieve coast and skin irritation and a dog food with very minimal ingredients to try. Gave it a week, but my lil one was still allergic, went back exchanged for a full bag of the "next in line" food combo, gave it a week, went back and had to exchange again (poor puppy!). They encouraged me and let me know she'd get better. Welp 3rd times a charm! Prices are great, I pay about 10 bucks more for a large bag, but this is way better quality, my nuggets eat less, have incredible energy, and allergies are gone! To sum it up, if you want the very best for your 4 legged family member, go to Paws!<//Text>

<time>1598750357127< /time>< review>
There was some tables outside if you really wanted to eat your food in the open air, but they only seat 2 people so don't take the whole familyüòÖ
The food was good and freshly made, NOT just sitting in a food warmer waiting to be put out like other burger joints. This place is better then fast food but has similar prices.
ü§†I HIGHLY recommend the Asad burrito and texan burger, and funnel fries. Seriously it was so delicious, this is definitely going to be a normal spot for us.
This DOCS is NOT ON MAIN STREET, where all the other restaurants are and its just a little bit hidden so keep you eyes peeled for it when driving or Google maps it, but 10/10 would recommend..<//review>

< text>
I went to Moxie on a recommendation from a friend, when we found out that our newly-purchased house had a massive community of brown widows living in a bush.  They were able to send a team over the day after my call - less than 24 hours.  Sean was the lead tech, accompanied by Mitch.  Both were lovely and thorough.  They started with a walk-around to identify edible plants and scope out the place, and then Mitch took care of the outdoors while Sean walked through indoors and sprayed the bottom of the walls.  They were great about finding problem areas - both in terms of things like nuking an active nest of daddy-long-legs in the garage, and lots of preventative care.  Sean explained the whole process to me, and was extremely clear and professional.

The company also has some great policies.  I signed up for a quarterly plan, which gave me this initial visit, plus 4 quarterly maintenance visits beginning a month from now.  This includes the garage.  Also, if we find infestations/activity at any point between visits, we can call and any upkeep/redos are covered.  We're just moving in, this didn't apply, but they also clean under patio furniture and such.  The company does an over-the-phone activation - great process, but be aware it will happen.  I was caught off-guard on a conference call when they tried first.  As long as you're free, this is really easy though - they have a form that you can sign online, including with a mouse/trackpad, that goes to their system in about 2 minutes once you've signed.

Update: they have now been our pest company for over a year, and they are great.  We've called them in for ant problems and the techs are always professional, polite, and effective.</text>

They came around the neighborhood with a special if we signed up with their services so my wife and I signed up with them which was the biggest mistake. They send out some kid to do the job, we have two young children at the time my daughter was 2 months old and my son was a little over two years old. The so called technician told me and my wife we should take the kids out for a few hours so my wife did just that. The technician was finished so a few hours later my wife comes home with the kids she goes into my son's room and finds a brass canister filled with fluid so she calls me to the room I immediately knew what it was it was the pesticide he was spraying in the house the same one we had to take the kids out of the house for a few hours so I immediately brought it outside a couple of hours later the technician comes  by apologizing so I give the canister back to him.       Second problem is we were still having problems with rodents so they came out more than a few times to try and fix the problem telling me it's a process. So I called another company  and in less than two weeks problem is gone.
Third problem is I caught the technician not doing all he said he was and showed him on video so he made up some stories and he would put extra on lawn, ooookkkkkk.
Fourth problem is I tell the lady from moxie when she called that I not going to be home on Saturday and that I will call them back when I'm available, she said okay. A little while later I get an email stating that they were going to come out on Saturday so I emailed them back and said no I just talked to someone and I'm saying it again in my email, a short time later I get another email basically telling me I don't care what you say per your agreement with our company we will be sending a technician to your home. So I sent another email telling them that I will call you when I'm home I would like to be home  considering the events that took place with your guy's services. I told her that with all the things that happened I would be a fool to let them back in or around my house she replied with the owner will look this over and decide what he wants to do with our agreement. It's real simple get some good quality employee's that know what the're doing and learn some customer service skills. BUYER BEWARE</Text>
